{
  "id": "019d332c-1e9f-7433-88dd-95369d21ce9e",
  "content": "# Claude Code Auth in Docker-in-Docker: Verified Findings (2026-03-28)\n\n## Corrected Finding\n`.credentials.json` alone IS sufficient for Claude Code auth. No `.claude.json` needed. Tested with fresh node:22-bookworm container.\n\n## The Real Problem: DinD Mount Paths\nWhen a devcontainer tries to mount `/root/.claude/.credentials.json` into a spoke container via `docker run -v`, Docker daemon resolves the path against the HOST filesystem, not the container filesystem. The file doesn't exist on the host at that path. Docker silently creates an empty directory instead of failing.\n\n## Solution for Spokes\nPipe credentials into spoke containers at creation time:\n```bash\ncat /root/.claude/.credentials.json | docker run -i ... bash -c 'mkdir -p /root/.claude && cat > /root/.claude/.credentials.json && chmod 600 /root/.claude/.credentials.json'\n```\n\n## Test Results\n- Fresh container + `.credentials.json` piped in = AUTHENTICATED\n- Fresh container + no credentials = \"Not logged in\"\n- Subscription type: \"max\" (Opus access confirmed)\n- Supersedes earlier incorrect finding about needing `.claude.json`",
  "source_version": "mcp",
